They delve into the risks of deflation and the unparalleled scalability of AI, highlighting companies like Streamex (STEX), DG Power X (DGXX), and Wrap Technologies (WRAP) as undervalued picks with significant upside potential. The hosts also touch upon the impact of politics on investing decisions, particularly under a potential Trump administration.

title: Walmart Inc. (WMT) Price Target Increased at Oppenheimer as Firm Eyes Solid Q4

(WMT) from $125 to $140, maintaining an Outperform rating, based on expectations for a strong Q4 and solid top-line momentum. title: Ziff Davis Sues Google Over Alleged Ad-Tech Monopoly
summary: Digital publishing company Ziff Davis Inc. has filed an antitrust lawsuit against Google, accusing the tech giant of monopolizing the online advertising technology market. The lawsuit alleges that Google uses its dominant position to force publishers to sell ad space through its systems, leading to reduced revenue for publishers and stifling competition. Ziff Davis, which owns brands like CNET and PCMag, claims that despite its significant online presence, it has not proportionally benefited from the $200 billion digital advertising market due to Google's alleged practices.

title: Is B2Gold Corp. (BTG) One of the Most Undervalued Gold Stocks to Buy According to Analysts?
summary: B2Gold Corp. (BTG) is considered one of the most undervalued gold stocks by analysts, with CIBC increasing its price target to $6.50 based on revised gold price forecasts. Despite short-term production hurdles at its Goose mine, the company projects significant ramp-up and is advancing strategic expansions like the Antelope underground deposit. B2Gold is a Canadian gold producer with operations across Mali, the Philippines, and Namibia, and is also involved in a project in Colombia.

title: Europe spending on sovereign cloud infrastructure to triple from 2025-2027 - Gartner
summary: European spending on sovereign cloud Infrastructure as a Service (IaaS) is projected to triple between 2025 and 2027, with spending rising to $12.6 billion in 2026 and $23.1 billion in 2027. This increase is driven by a growing concern for digital and technological independence amid geopolitical tensions and reliance on US or Chinese hyperscalers. Globally, sovereign cloud spending is expected to reach $80 billion in 2026, with 20 percent of new spending shifting existing workloads to local providers and 80 percent supporting new digital solutions or modernizing legacy workloads.

title: Elizabeth Warren 'Pushing For Answers' After Google Turns Gemini Into An AI Shopping Assistant: Senator Says It Could Lead To Consumer Manipulation

This move is part of an escalating AI shopping race, with competitors like OpenAI and Amazon also developing similar tools.

While US-owned "sovereign" cloud services exist, their true sovereignty is questioned, suggesting partnerships with local providers might be a better approach for hyperscalers.

summary: Ero Copper Corp. (NYSE:ERO) has received a consensus "Moderate Buy" rating from nineteen analysts, with an average 12-month price target of $32.50. The company, focused on copper production in Brazil, has seen varied analyst ratings recently, including upgrades and a downgrade, and exhibits a market capitalization of $3.31 billion.

title: D-Wave Quantum Expands Dual-Platform Ambitions With New Contracts And U.S. Hub
summary: D-Wave Quantum (NYSE:QBTS) is expanding its operations and technological capabilities by acquiring Quantum Circuits Inc., adopting a dual-platform approach with both annealing and gate-model quantum technologies. The company is also establishing a new U.S. headquarters and R&D hub in Boca Raton, Florida, signaling a significant push to commercialize its quantum solutions and scale its presence.

title: IBM Introduces Autonomous Storage with New FlashSystem Portfolio Powered by Agentic AI
summary: IBM has launched the next generation of its FlashSystem portfolio, featuring agentic AI to usher in an era of autonomous storage. These new systems, including FlashSystem 5600, 7600, and 9600, significantly reduce manual storage management efforts by up to 90% and offer up to 40% greater data efficiency. A new fifth-generation FlashCore Module is engineered for real-time ransomware detection within one minute, enhanced resiliency, and data management, transforming storage into an intelligent, always-on layer.

title: MKS (MKSI) to Release Earnings on Tuesday
summary: MKS Instruments (NASDAQ:MKSI) is set to release its Q4 2025 earnings after market close on Tuesday, February 17th, with analysts expecting $2.25 EPS and $1.0154 billion in revenue. The company's stock opened at $250.60, currently trading near its 52-week high, and holds a "Moderate Buy" rating from analysts with a consensus target price of $231.50. Recent insider activity shows a director selling 300 shares, while institutional investors have adjusted their holdings.

title: Melius Downgrades Microsoft (MSFT) to Hold, Flags AI Capex and Cash Flow Risks
summary: Melius analyst Ben Reitzes downgraded Microsoft (MSFT) from Buy to Hold with a $430 price target, citing concerns about AI-related capital expenditure and cash flow risks. The analyst believes Microsoft's 365 business faces threats from AI, requiring increased spending to compete with Amazon and Google, which could further impact free cash flow. Additionally, Melius noted the slow progress of Microsoft's AI assistant, Copilot, suggesting it may struggle against competitors and affect growth and margins in the Productivity segment, despite valuation concerns related to revised free cash flow estimates.

title: UBS Group CEO Ermotti Touts “Very Strong” 2025 Progress, $7T Assets and Credit Suisse Integration Wins
summary: UBS Group CEO Sergio Ermotti highlighted the bank's "very strong" progress in 2025, with invested assets exceeding $7 trillion and broad-based profit growth. The move positions TeraWulf as a key player in the energy and compute infrastructure sector, attracting interest from major tech companies like Google.

title: Narrow Drawdown?
summary: Equity volatility is increasing, but this is largely due to a decline in mega-cap technology stocks which are driving down the S&P 500. This trend is expected to continue given the resilience of the U.S. economy, highlighting the importance of diversification.

title: United Rentals (NYSE:URI) EVP William Grace Sells 1,498 Shares of Stock
summary: United Rentals EVP William Grace sold 1,498 shares of URI stock on February 3rd for over $1.18 million, reducing his stake by 17.9%. title: State regulators OK Dominion project near Hallsley area of Chesterfield

The project, which will include 1.5 miles of lines running along the subdivision's edge, is intended to power future data centers in the area, including a planned Google facility. The State Corporation Commission approved the shortest of three proposed routes and ruled that burying the lines would be too costly.

title: Gartner Says Worldwide Sovereign Cloud IaaS Spending Will Total $80B in 2026
summary: Gartner forecasts that worldwide sovereign cloud Infrastructure as a Service (IaaS) spending will reach $80 billion in 2026, marking a 35.6% increase from 2025. This surge is driven by countries outside the U.S. and China seeking digital and technological independence, with governments and regulated industries being the primary purchasers. The increasing demand for "geopatriation" projects is expected to shift 20% of current workloads from global to local cloud providers, pressuring hyperscalers to address national sovereignty concerns.

title: The Truth About TripAdvisor Inc: Why Everyone Is Checking In (But Should You?)
summary: TripAdvisor Inc. (TRIP) is experiencing a resurgence in popularity, particularly on social media platforms like TikTok and YouTube, for exposing hotel discrepancies and finding cheaper travel options. It evaluates TripAdvisor's strengths in reviews and experiences against competitors like Google Reviews and major booking sites, concluding that while it's a strong "truth check" for travelers, investors should conduct thorough due diligence before considering TRIP stock.

title: What's driving Procter & Gamble's monster start to 2026 — and how it can continue

The company's performance is further bolstered by improving fundamentals, including strength in emerging markets, a weaker U.S. dollar, and lower oil prices, all contributing to better margins and sales.

title: Invesco QQQ $QQQ Shares Sold by Yahav Achim Ve Achayot Provident Funds Management Co Ltd.

(NASDAQ:GOOGL) recently achieved a legal victory where a federal judge limited damages to $425 million in a data tracking lawsuit, significantly less than the $31 billion initially sought. Analysts are optimistic about Alphabet's AI-driven growth in Search, YouTube, and Cloud ahead of its Q4 earnings report, though insider selling and elevated options market volatility suggest potential near-term risks. title: Amazon stock (AMZN) climbs after-hours as earnings loom and fresh filing hits tape

title: Scaling Automation Without Complexity: Strategies for Streamlined Growth
summary: This article discusses strategies for scaling automation effectively without introducing unnecessary complexity. It emphasizes starting with simple, high-volume tasks, empowering citizen developers, and using cloud-native architectures. The author also highlights the importance of centralizing control, standardizing processes before automating, and leveraging AI to ensure streamlined growth and avoid common pitfalls like automating broken processes or neglecting the human element.

title: The Algorithm as Architect: Inside Amazon’s 14,000-Role AI Displacement Strategy
summary: Amazon is undergoing a radical transformation, cutting 14,000 corporate jobs and replacing middle management and operational oversight with AI-driven systems like "Project Dawn," Amazon Q Developer, and Blue Jay robotics. This strategic shift, driven by CEO Andy Jassy’s efficiency mandate, signals a move from human-led management to AI-orchestrated operations, setting a precedent for other tech giants. While it promises significant cost savings and agility, it also raises concerns about the erosion of middle-class corporate roles and the long-term societal impact of large-scale AI-driven job displacement.

title: SAP SE (SAP): A Bull Case Theory

The company's competitive advantage lies in its integrated suite approach, strategic differentiation through capital discipline, and agentic AI integration. Despite challenges like declining software license revenue and market volatility, management is optimistic about future revenue growth and cloud adoption, with AI-led RISE migrations expected to accelerate growth.

title: Alphabet (GOOGL) Earnings Preview - New All-Time Highs Ahead?

This transaction comes amidst varied analyst perspectives on Wayfair, including a collaboration with Google for a Universal Commerce Protocol, Mizuho's Outperform rating with a $130 target, Jefferies' downgrade to Hold due to valuation concerns, and Truist Securities' reiterated Buy rating with a $120 target.

title: RBC Capital initiates Astera Labs stock with Outperform rating, $225 target
summary: RBC Capital has initiated coverage on Astera Labs (NASDAQ:ALAB) with an Outperform rating and a $225 price target. The firm cited strong near-term fundamentals from core retimer growth and Scorpio-P switch ramps, along with the expected 2026 ramp of Astera’s Scorpio-X scale-up switch, as key drivers for its positive outlook. Despite recent stock underperformance due to concerns about networking standards and Google's TPU advancements, RBC Capital justifies its premium valuation based on Astera Labs' projected 40% growth rate, a $10-15 billion serviceable available market, and gross margins over 70%.

title: What's Going On With Shopify Stock?
summary: Shopify (NYSE: SHOP) stock saw an uplift on Thursday, aligning with a positive broader market trend, especially in the technology sector. Despite no specific news, favorable market sentiment and strong performance metrics, including a 53.59% increase over 12 months, contributed to its rise. Analysts maintain a "Buy" rating with an average price target of $171.07, anticipating strong earnings and revenue growth in the upcoming report.

title: Fund delivering 25.7% return and 8.1% payout tops S&P 500 in 2025
summary: Adams Diversified Equity Fund (NYSE: ADX) announced its 2025 performance, reporting a market-price total return of 25.7% and a NAV total return of 18.9%, outperforming the S&P 500's 17.9%. The fund also distributed $1.85 per share, equating to an 8.1% annual distribution rate on NAV, and saw its net assets increase to over $3 billion. Information Technology remains its largest sector holding, with top positions in companies like NVIDIA, Apple, and Microsoft.

title: Gene Munster Says Apple's Move From OpenAI's ChatGPT To Google Gemini Significantly Raises Chances Of New Siri Succeeding: 'Nice Job'
summary: Gene Munster, managing partner at Deepwater Asset Management, believes Apple's decision to switch from OpenAI's ChatGPT to Google Gemini for its new Siri significantly increases the chances of Siri's success. He praised Apple CEO Tim Cook for addressing Siri's long-standing weaknesses and leveraging the partnership for future growth in devices and services. This move signals a more serious approach from Apple towards enhancing Apple Intelligence, according to Munster.

title: Run Oracle databases inside AWS, Azure and Google Cloud data centers
summary: Oracle announced an expansion of its multicloud capabilities, allowing Oracle Database services running on Oracle Cloud Infrastructure (OCI) to be deployed directly within AWS, Google Cloud, and Microsoft Azure data centers. This initiative, including offerings like Oracle Database@AWS, Oracle Database@Azure, and Oracle Database@Google Cloud, aims to simplify cloud migration, offer unified administration, and provide flexible purchasing options for customers. Oracle plans further global expansion to meet the growing demand for its database services across multiple cloud environments.

title: Barlow Wealth Partners Fully Exits Position in Sprouts Farmers Market Stock Valued at $16.7 Million
summary: Barlow Wealth Partners, LLC has fully liquidated its 154,705 shares in Sprouts Farmers Market (NASDAQ:SFM), a transaction valued at an estimated $16.72 million. This move comes as Sprouts Farmers Market's stock has declined significantly and faces class-action lawsuits regarding misleading statements about its growth potential. The firm's top holdings now include Alphabet, Microsoft, and Nvidia.

title: Why Lam Research (LRCX) Stock Is Trading Up Today
summary: Lam Research's stock is trading up today after several financial firms showed strong confidence in the company. Wells Fargo upgraded its rating and significantly boosted its price target, while RBC Capital Markets initiated coverage with an "Outperform" rating. Morgan Stanley also raised its price target, collectively signaling strong investor confidence in the semiconductor equipment maker.

title: A Look At TransUnion (TRU) Valuation After AI Marketing Breakthrough With Actable
summary: TransUnion (TRU) is being evaluated after its TruAudience Marketing Solutions, in collaboration with Actable, showed strong results in an AI marketing campaign. Despite a recent short-term share price increase, the company experienced a decline over the past year. Analysts indicate TRU is undervalued by 19.8% with a fair value of US$106.60, yet its P/E ratio is higher than industry averages, suggesting the market is already pricing in future growth.

title: Papa Johns bolsters in-store tech with AI platforms
summary: Papa Johns is enhancing its in-store technology by partnering with Par Technology Corporation to deploy Par POS and Par OPS platforms across its U.S. restaurants. This initiative aims to create a "faster, more intelligent and connected" experience for customers and operators by integrating AI-powered features for labor, inventory, and restaurant management. The full rollout of these enterprise solutions is planned for all U.S. corporate and franchise locations by the end of 2027.

title: Cisco Announces its Second Annual AI Summit Featuring the Builders of the AI Economy
summary: Cisco is holding its second annual AI Summit on February 3, 2026, in San Francisco and online, featuring influential leaders in the AI industry. The event, hosted by Cisco's Chair & CEO Chuck Robbins and President & Chief Product Officer Jeetu Patel, will include discussions on how AI is being built, governed, and its real-world impact, covering various aspects from compute and venture capital to geopolitics. The full program will be livestreamed globally and will feature speakers from companies like NVIDIA, OpenAI, AWS, and Google.

title: Wells Fargo upgrades Broadcom, Analog Devices and Monolithic Power Systems to Overweight
summary: Wells Fargo has upgraded Broadcom, Analog Devices, and Monolithic Power Systems from Equal-weight to Overweight. This action led to an increase in share prices for all three companies during early market trading on Thursday. The upgrades are attributed to factors such as Broadcom's partnership with Google, strong bookings for Analog Devices, and anticipated growth in Monolithic Power Systems' enterprise data segment.

title: Next phase of Five9-Google partnership targets large enterprises
summary: Five9 and Google Cloud have expanded their partnership, introducing a new joint Enterprise CX AI solution aimed at large enterprises. This collaboration builds on Five9's established use of Google Cloud infrastructure, allowing for deeper integration of AI technologies like Gemini and Vertex AI into Five9's platform. While this expands Google's enterprise offerings with Five9, UJET remains Google's exclusive OEM CCaaS partner, continuing to secure large enterprise deals alongside smaller market wins.

title: Wing Drone Delivery Takes Off at 5 Houston-Area Walmart Stores
summary: Wing, Alphabet's drone delivery service, has expanded its operations to five Walmart Supercenters in the Greater Houston area, offering rapid delivery of essential items. This move is part of an ambitious 2026 expansion plan with Walmart, aiming to add 150 stores and reach 40 million new customers, with a target of 270 locations by 2027. The future growth of drone delivery largely hinges on the FAA's proposed Part 108 regulations regarding Beyond Visual Line of Sight (BVLOS) operations, which would allow for expanded drone operational range.

title: Electronic Arts Inc. $EA Shares Acquired by Walter Public Investments Inc.
summary: Walter Public Investments Inc. recently increased its stake in Electronic Arts Inc. (NASDAQ:EA) by 41.7%, acquiring an additional 14,134 shares to own a total of 48,017 shares valued at $9.685 million. Other institutional investors like State Street Corp, Ninety One UK Ltd, and Ameriprise Financial Inc. also significantly boosted their holdings in EA. Despite substantial institutional ownership, Electronic Arts faces mixed analyst ratings, with most analysts holding a "Hold" recommendation and a consensus target price of $181.21.

title: OVERSEA CHINESE BANKING Corp Ltd Sells 24,478 Shares of Walmart Inc. $WMT
summary: OVERSEA CHINESE BANKING Corp Ltd significantly reduced its stake in Walmart Inc. by selling 24,478 shares, now holding 145,168 shares valued at approximately $14.96 million. This divestment comes despite Walmart exceeding earnings estimates, setting positive FY2026 guidance, and benefiting from a Google/AI partnership, strong market momentum, and analyst price target increases. However, the article also notes recent insider selling and some valuation concerns amidst the positive news.

title: OpenAI made 'conscious decision' to sit out Apple Siri deal: report (OPENAI:Private)
summary: OpenAI reportedly made a "conscious decision" not to partner with Apple for its updated Siri, despite speculation that Apple passed on the ChatGPT maker. Instead, Apple chose Google's Gemini models for a multi-year partnership involving significant payments. OpenAI's decision was influenced by its focus on developing its own AI hardware and surpassing other large tech companies, though it continues to partner with Apple through ChatGPT integrations and is recruiting former Apple talent.

title: Broadwind Energy, Inc. (NASDAQ:BWEN) Sees Significant Drop in Short Interest
summary: Broadwind Energy, Inc. (NASDAQ:BWEN) experienced a significant 41% decrease in short interest in December, with total short interest falling to 53,729 shares. Institutional investors hold 33.27% of the company's stock, and several funds recently adjusted their positions. Despite opening down 10% on Thursday, the company recently beat EPS and revenue estimates, and analysts maintain a "Moderate Buy" rating with a target price of $4.50.

title: WestEnd Advisors LLC Has $53.84 Million Stock Holdings in Alphabet Inc. $GOOGL
summary: WestEnd Advisors LLC reduced its stake in Alphabet Inc. by 10.7% in Q3, now holding 221,451 shares valued at $53.84 million, representing 1.3% of its portfolio. Alphabet (NASDAQ:GOOGL) reported strong Q3 earnings, exceeding revenue and EPS estimates, trading near its 52-week high with a $4.05 trillion market cap and a "Moderate Buy" consensus analyst rating. The company's stock is driven by AI advancements but faces operational and regulatory challenges, alongside significant insider selling activity.

title: Uber's 2025 Reality Check: 3 Shifts Investors Can't Ignore
summary: Uber has reached a pivotal point in 2025, moving from a speculative growth story to a profitable and essential infrastructure company. Three key shifts are driving this transformation: its mobility business now consistently generates profits and free cash flow, Uber Eats is expanding beyond food delivery into diverse local commerce, and a high-margin advertising business is significantly improving its earnings quality. These developments demonstrate Uber's progress toward sustainable profitability and solidifies its position for long-term value creation.

title: Clearway Signs Portfolio of Power Purchase Agreements with Google Totaling Nearly 1.2 GW Across Three States
summary: Clearway Energy Group has announced new long-term power purchase agreements with Google, totaling 1.17 GW across projects in Missouri, Texas, and West Virginia. These agreements will supply carbon-free energy to Google's data centers for up to 20 years, representing over $2.4 billion in energy infrastructure investment. The projects are anticipated to begin construction this year, with initial sites coming online in 2027 and 2028, further expanding Clearway's partnership with Google to a total of 1.24 GW.

title: Garmin Is Quietly Winning 2026 – But Is It Still Worth Your Money?
summary: This article evaluates whether Garmin wearables and its stock (GRMN) are still a worthwhile investment in 2026, comparing its offerings to Apple Watch and Samsung. It highlights Garmin's strengths in deep fitness metrics, battery life, and durability for serious athletes, while also analyzing the company's diversified business segments for stock investors. The author concludes that Garmin is a "cop" (worth buying) for dedicated fitness enthusiasts and a research candidate for investors looking for stable hardware brands.

title: These Funds Hold the Largest Stakes in Alphabet Stock
summary: Alphabet's stock surge, driven by AI enthusiasm and the release of Gemini 3, has significantly impacted funds heavily invested in the company. The Provident Trust Strategy Fund and Fidelity OTC Portfolio hold the largest stakes, with several ESG-focused funds also appearing on the list of top holders. This performance has propelled Alphabet to become the world's second-largest company, highlighting the strong returns for funds with major allocations to its stock.

title: 9,723 Shares in Alphabet Inc. $GOOG Acquired by Steinberganna Wealth Management
summary: Steinberganna Wealth Management acquired 9,723 shares of Alphabet Inc. (NASDAQ:GOOG) in Q3, valued at approximately $2.37 million, making it their 19th largest position. This acquisition comes as institutional ownership in Alphabet rises to 27.26%, and several other hedge funds have also adjusted their holdings. The report also highlights recent insider selling, bullish analyst sentiment with raised price targets, and Alphabet's current market cap of $4.06 trillion following strong Q3 earnings.

title: Alphabet Inc. $GOOGL Shares Sold by LS Investment Advisors LLC
summary: LS Investment Advisors LLC reduced its stake in Alphabet (NASDAQ:GOOGL) by 6.6% in the third quarter, selling 4,513 shares and retaining 63,793 shares valued at approximately $15.5 million. This sale represents their 14th largest holding and 2.2% of their portfolio. Despite insider selling from CEO Sundar Pichai and CAO Amie Thuener O'toole, Wall Street analysts maintain a "Moderate Buy" consensus rating with a target price of $326.31, as Alphabet's market cap tops $4 trillion driven by AI and Gemini momentum.

title: Microsoft taps India’s Varaha for durable carbon removal offtake
summary: Microsoft has partnered with the Indian startup Varaha to secure over 100,000 tons of carbon dioxide removal credits through 2029. This initiative will convert cotton crop waste into biochar, which stores carbon and reduces air pollution, involving 40,000-45,000 smallholder farmers in Maharashtra. The deal expands Microsoft's carbon removal portfolio as the company seeks to offset increased emissions from its growing AI and cloud operations, aiming for carbon-negativity by 2030.

title: Alphabet Inc. $GOOGL Stock Position Lifted by Railway Pension Investments Ltd
summary: Railway Pension Investments Ltd significantly increased its stake in Alphabet Inc. ($GOOGL) by 79.8% in Q3 2025, making it the fund's second-largest holding. Despite recent insider selling, analysts are raising price targets for Alphabet, citing strong earnings and advancements in artificial intelligence, with the company’s market cap recently surpassing $4 trillion. The article also highlights key positive and negative news impacting Alphabet, including strategic wins for Gemini and challenges related to power grid bottlenecks for data centers.

title: Motco Lowers Holdings in Alphabet Inc. $GOOGL
summary: Motco reduced its stake in Alphabet Inc. (NASDAQ:GOOGL) by 2.8% in Q3, selling 3,197 shares to hold 111,392 shares valued at approximately $27.08 million, making it their fourth largest holding. This comes amidst significant insider selling by CEO Sundar Pichai and others, though analysts widely maintain a "Moderate Buy" rating with a consensus target price of $326.31. Alphabet recently surpassed a $4 trillion market capitalization, buoyed by accelerating AI commercialization and strategic wins like Apple's selection of Gemini.

title: Apple Inc. $AAPL Shares Bought by Los Angeles Capital Management LLC
summary: Los Angeles Capital Management LLC significantly increased its stake in Apple Inc. ($AAPL) by 10.8% in the third quarter, making Apple its second-largest holding. This comes amidst several analyst price target raises and upgrades, with a consensus "Moderate Buy" rating. Strategic catalysts, including Apple's partnership with Google's Gemini for AI features and the launch of Creator Studio, are expected to boost Services revenue and device refresh cycles.

title: Greenspring Advisors LLC Makes New Investment in Alphabet Inc. $GOOGL
summary: Greenspring Advisors LLC recently acquired 2,933 shares of Alphabet Inc. (GOOGL) in the third quarter, a new investment valued at approximately $713,000. This investment comes as Alphabet reported strong Q3 earnings, surpassing analyst expectations with $2.87 EPS and $102.35 billion revenue, pushing its market capitalization over $4 trillion. The company also disclosed a quarterly dividend of $0.21, and analysts maintain a "Moderate Buy" rating with an average target price of $326.31.

title: Five9 & Google Cloud launch unified AI contact centre CX
summary: Five9 and Google Cloud have expanded their partnership, launching a joint enterprise customer experience AI offering. This solution integrates Five9's contact center platform with Google's Gemini and Vertex AI services, targeting large organizations needing to manage customer engagement across multiple channels. The collaboration aims to provide a unified user experience for agents and improve personalized customer interactions through automation and data.

title: L1 Capital International Strategy: Uber (UBER) is a ‘Battleground’ Company
summary: L1 Capital International Fund highlighted Uber Technologies, Inc. (NYSE: UBER) in its Q4 2025 investor letter, describing it as a "battleground" company. While Uber leads in ridesharing and meal delivery and is positioning itself for the autonomous vehicle future, L1 Capital views it as a higher-risk, higher-return investment, maintaining a smaller position. The fund emphasizes that conviction in AI alone isn't sufficient for successful investing, despite strong stock market performance in 2025.

title: Commonwealth Equity Services LLC Sells 220,783 Shares of Alphabet Inc. $GOOGL
summary: Commonwealth Equity Services LLC reduced its stake in Alphabet Inc. (NASDAQ:GOOGL) by 8.2% in the third quarter, selling 220,783 shares but still holding 2,467,049 shares valued at $599.74 million. Despite this insider selling, which totaled 189,309 shares by executives like Sundar Pichai and John Kent Walker, analyst sentiment remains largely bullish with a "Moderate Buy" rating and an average price target of $326.31. Alphabet's stock also benefits from AI momentum, strategic wins like Apple adopting Gemini, and faster product commercialization, pushing its market cap past $4 trillion.

title: Google Executive Warns US Power Grid Isn't Keeping Up With AI Data Center Expansion, Describes 'Number One Challenge' On The Network
summary: A Google executive has raised concerns that the U.S. power grid is struggling to keep pace with the rapid expansion of AI data centers, citing transmission bottlenecks that can cause years-long delays for grid connections. Google is exploring temporary solutions like colocation, placing data centers next to power plants, while striving for eventual grid integration. The growing energy demand from AI is projected to significantly increase global electricity consumption by 2035.

title: Trade of The Day – Alphabet Inc Class A (NASDAQ: GOOGL)
summary: Phillip Securities Research has identified Alphabet Inc Class A (NASDAQ: GOOGL) as a "TECHNICAL BUY" with a current price of US$335.84. The recommended strategy includes a buy price at US$335.84, a stop loss at US$321.50, and a take profit target at US$365.84. Access to the full PDF report and detailed analysis requires a premium content subscription.

title: Apple Inc. (NASDAQ:AAPL) Receives Average Rating of "Moderate Buy" from Analysts
summary: Apple Inc. (NASDAQ:AAPL) has received an average rating of "Moderate Buy" from 37 analysts, with a consensus one-year price target of $284.07. Recent developments include a partnership with Google's Gemini for Siri and the launch of Creator Studio, which are expected to boost Services monetization and device refresh cycles. Despite some near-term risks like chipboard material shortages and advocacy pressure, Apple recently surpassed quarterly EPS and revenue estimates and maintains a market capitalization of almost $3.8 trillion.

title: Alphabet Inc. (NASDAQ:GOOGL) Receives Consensus Recommendation of "Moderate Buy" from Analysts
summary: Alphabet Inc. (NASDAQ:GOOGL) has received a "Moderate Buy" consensus recommendation from 52 analysts, with an average 12-month price target of $326.31, driven by AI momentum and strategic wins like Apple choosing Gemini for Siri. Despite recent significant insider selling totaling approximately $57.7 million, Alphabet's stock has surpassed a $4 trillion market capitalization and recently beat quarterly EPS and revenue estimates. The company also announced a quarterly dividend of $0.21 per share.

title: Here's an AI Stock Nobody's Talking About -- But Should Be
summary: The article highlights InterDigital (NASDAQ: IDCC) as an overlooked AI stock that focuses on intellectual property and foundational technology rather than consumer-facing products. The company develops cutting-edge tech, obtains patents, and licenses its innovations across various industries, including wireless networks and AI video coding. InterDigital's business model has led to significant growth in its patent portfolio, establishing it as a leader in setting global technology standards.

title: Taseko (TGB) Climbs 11.8% on Looming Copper Site Operations
summary: Taseko Mines Limited (NYSEAmerican:TGB) saw its stock surge by 11.81% due to the impending start of operations at its Florence Copper mine in Arizona, completing construction and moving to wellfield operations and commissioning. The company expects first copper cathode production within weeks and reported improved copper and molybdenum production from its Gibraltar mine in the latter half of 2025. Taseko's CEO anticipates more consistent and higher overall copper production in 2026.

title: Nvidia vs. Alphabet: Which Is the Better AI Growth Stock for 2026?
summary: This article analyzes Nvidia and Alphabet as AI growth stocks for 2026, comparing their business models, financial performance, and valuations. While Nvidia is praised for its explosive growth in AI infrastructure, Alphabet is highlighted for its diversified AI integration across various platforms and expanding Google Cloud profitability. The author ultimately suggests Alphabet as a better long-term investment due to its more diversified and less cyclical business model, despite acknowledging risks associated with both companies.

title: Crescent Biopharma Advances CR-001 Cancer Trial Into First-in-Human Stage
summary: Crescent Biopharma, Inc. (CBIO) has announced the advancement of its CR-001 cancer trial into the first-in-human stage with a Phase 1/2 study. The trial aims to evaluate the safety, pharmacokinetics, pharmacodynamics, and antitumor activity of CR-001 in adults with locally advanced or metastatic solid tumors. While the study is currently in the "Not Yet Recruiting" phase, this marks a significant value inflection point for the biotech firm, potentially influencing future capital raises or partnerships.

title: FEDERATED HERMES, INC. Reduces Stake in Arcturus Therapeutics Ho
summary: FEDERATED HERMES, INC. reduced its stake in Arcturus Therapeutics Holdings Inc by 29.62%, selling 1,390,420 shares at $6.13 each. While Arcturus appears undervalued with a GF Value of $11.28, its low profitability, financial distress indicated by an Altman Z score of 0.28, and a Piotroski F-Score of 2 warrant a cautious outlook for investors. This strategic move by Federated Hermes suggests a reevaluation of the biotechnology company's future prospects despite a significant post-transaction gain in ARCT's stock price.

title: F5 EVP Fountain sells $294k in shares By Investing.com
summary: F5's Executive Vice President, Thomas Dean Fountain, sold 1,110 shares of F5, INC. stock for a total of $294,150. This transaction was part of a Rule 10b5-1 trading plan. The article also highlights recent company developments, including new AI security solutions, a collaboration with Google Cloud for F5 NGINXaaS, and analyst rating upgrades following a security incident.

title: F5 EVP Fountain sells $294k in shares
summary: F5 (NASDAQ:FFIV) Executive Vice President Thomas Dean Fountain sold 1,110 shares of company stock for $294,150 on January 12, 2026. This transaction was part of a pre-established trading plan. The article also highlights recent positive developments for F5, including new AI security solutions, a collaboration with Google Cloud, and analyst rating upgrades despite a recent security breach.

title: 2 EV Stocks That Could Be Heading for $0, and 1 With Multibagger Potential Left
summary: The U.S. EV market faced headwinds in 2025, with sales down 1% due to tariffs and the expiration of tax credits. While Rivian and Lucid struggle with high losses despite revenue growth, Tesla, despite a challenging year, shows strong fundamentals and promising Q3 2025 revenue growth, positioning it as the most viable long-term investment among American EV manufacturers.

title: CIO survey shows 3.8% increase to software budgets in 2026: Morgan Stanley
summary: A Morgan Stanley survey of Chief Information Officers (CIOs) projects a 3.8% year-over-year increase in enterprise software budgets for 2026. Microsoft (MSFT) is expected to maintain its leading market share position, indicating continued dominance in the software sector.

title: Tesla puts full self-driving behind a monthly paywall
summary: Tesla has announced that its Full Self-Driving (Supervised) software will transition to a monthly subscription model starting February 14, discontinuing the one-time purchase option. This move, driven in part by a recent shareholder-approved pay package for CEO Elon Musk tied to achieving 10 million FSD subscriptions, coincides with increased competition and scrutiny over the software's capabilities and marketing. The change reflects Tesla's ongoing strategy to monetize its advanced driver-assistance features amidst challenges in its EV market share and robotaxi development.

title: After Apple Deal, Is Google — Not OpenAI — Now the Premier AI Stock?
summary: Google's new partnership with Apple, integrating its Gemini 3 AI model into iPhones, is poised to reshape the AI competitive landscape. This deal strengthens Google's position in search and cloud services, propelling it as a premier AI stock over rivals like OpenAI. Analysts maintain a "Strong Buy" consensus for Alphabet stock, citing its AI-driven trajectory and potential for significant market share gains.

title: Cloud outages expected to be the new normal in 2026
summary: Following widespread cloud outages in 2025 that led to significant financial losses and eroded customer trust, businesses are bracing for a continuation of these disruptions in 2026. Experts suggest that a shift in hyperscaler investment towards AI-native data centers, away from legacy infrastructure, will contribute to this trend. Consequently, many organizations are exploring new strategies like smaller regional clouds, multi-cloud approaches, and "invisible" cloud architectures with AI-assisted failover to mitigate risks and avoid single points of failure.

title: Analysts Offer Insights on Communication Services Companies: Alphabet Class A (GOOGL) and Genius Sports Limited (GENI)
summary: Two analysts have offered bullish sentiments on communication services companies Alphabet Class A (GOOGL) and Genius Sports Limited (GENI). Ronald Josey from Citi reiterated a Buy rating on Alphabet with a $350.00 price target, while Patrick Scholes from Truist Financial maintained a Buy rating on Genius Sports Limited with a $10.23 price target. Both companies received a Strong Buy consensus from analysts.

title: Why Arm Holdings Stock Lost 11% in 2025
summary: Arm Holdings (NASDAQ: ARM) stock experienced a volatile 2025, ending the year down 11% despite delivering solid growth and benefiting from AI tailwinds. The stock's performance was influenced by its high valuation and concerns about an AI bubble, with fluctuations throughout the year including a jump due to involvement in the Stargate Project and later declines linked to market retreats and investor disappointment in guidance. Arm continues to expand its product portfolio with compute subsystems and has strong partnerships in cloud computing, guiding for continued revenue growth in the upcoming quarter.

title: Verizon outage: Users report stuck in SOS mode
summary: Verizon customers nationwide reported widespread service outages on January 14, with over 171,000 reports of mobile signal loss. Customers of other major carriers like AT&T and T-Mobile also experienced disruptions, though to a lesser extent. Verizon acknowledged the issue on social media and stated that engineers are working to resolve the problem.

title: Empire State Realty stock hits 52-week low at 5.92 USD
summary: Empire State Realty OP LP (ESBA) stock has fallen to a 52-week low of 5.92 USD, representing a 34.62% decrease over the past year. Despite facing a challenging real estate market, the company exhibits strong financial indicators such as a 16% free cash flow yield, an EV/EBITDA multiple of 11.58, and a consistent 13-year dividend payment history with a 2.29% yield. InvestingPro analysis suggests the stock is currently undervalued.

title: Cisco’s FY25 Purpose Report: A Letter from Fran Katsoudas
summary: Fran Katsoudas, Cisco's Chief People, Policy, and Purpose Officer, highlights the critical role of continuous learning in navigating the digital and AI-enabled economy, as detailed in Cisco's FY25 Purpose Report. The report emphasizes Cisco's internal investment in AI skills for employees, the global reach of Cisco Networking Academy, and collaborative efforts through the AI Workforce Consortium to prepare for future workforce needs. Katsoudas underscores that learning empowers individuals, drives organizational resilience, and shapes a secure, trusted, and inclusive future for all.

title: Cantor Fitzgerald Reduces PT on Amazon.com (AMZN) Stock
summary: Cantor Fitzgerald has reduced its price target for Amazon.com (AMZN) stock from $315 to $260, while maintaining an "Overweight" rating. Despite macroeconomic concerns, the firm sees a favorable outlook for global internet stocks into 2026, driven by AI entering a "Synergy phase" which could accelerate revenue growth and improve returns. Separately, Jefferies increased its price target for AMZN to $300, anticipating a reversal in negative sentiment due to accelerating AWS growth and AI capabilities.

title: Jim Cramer Says Cheesecake Factory Is “Way Too Cheap for a Very High-Quality Still Growth Company”
summary: Jim Cramer believes Cheesecake Factory (NASDAQ: CAKE) is undervalued, calling it "way too cheap for a very high-quality still growth company" given its 13 times earnings valuation and 14% year-to-date gain. He highlighted the company's strong management, unique value proposition through its diverse menu, and impressive unit-level margins. Despite his positive sentiment, Cramer advised caution before buying, suggesting investors wait for upcoming earnings reports due to management's historically conservative outlook that has sometimes led to stock dips even after strong quarters.

title: Is Amazon’s Cloud Unit Big Enough to Reaccelerate Share Gains?
summary: Amazon's cloud unit, Amazon Web Services (AWS), has seen its growth reaccelerate to 2022 levels, primarily driven by strong demand for artificial intelligence. CEO Andy Jassy highlighted the continued need for AI infrastructure and storage, which benefits AWS. The emergence of "physical AI" like humanoid robots and autonomous vehicles is expected to further boost cloud platform demand, making Amazon a promising stock for 2026 and beyond.

title: Northrop Grumman stock hits all-time high of 641.3 USD
summary: Northrop Grumman Corporation's (NYSE:NOC) stock reached an all-time high of $641.3, an 8.4% gain in the past week and a 35.48% increase over the past year. The company, with a market capitalization of $91.39 billion, has demonstrated strong financial health and investor confidence due to its performance in the defense sector, strategic initiatives, and consistent dividend payments for 55 consecutive years. Recent contract wins for advanced torpedoes and missile defense technologies underscore its market position, though InvestingPro suggests the stock is slightly overvalued.

title: FatPipe Inc Highlights Proven Fail-Proof Autonomous Vehicle Connectivity Solutions to Avoid Waymo San Francisco Outage-like Situations
summary: FatPipe Inc. addresses autonomous vehicle connectivity challenges by highlighting its fail-proof solutions, especially in light of recent Waymo outages in San Francisco. The company's technology, which seamlessly switches between GEO satellite, LEO satellite, and 4G/5G cellular networks, ensures continuous and resilient connectivity for autonomous operations. This approach has been proven through trials like Project Darwin, showing significant improvement in connectivity availability even with individual network gaps.

title: Is Yelp’s Earnings Beat With Slower Revenue Growth Altering The Investment Case For Yelp (YELP)?
summary: Yelp recently reported an earnings beat with revenues of US$376.0 million, a 4.4% year-on-year increase, and provided slightly higher full-year EBITDA guidance. Despite these positive results, Yelp exhibited the slowest revenue growth among its social networking peers, raising questions about its competitive position and growth profile. Analysts maintain a cautious outlook, with Morgan Stanley cutting its price target to US$28.00, reflecting concerns about the company's ability to reaccelerate demand from small business advertisers and prove durable value creation despite slower growth.

title: Supermicro Stock Slips 46% in 3 Months: Should You Buy, Sell, or Hold SMCI?
summary: Super Micro Computer (SMCI) stock has fallen significantly, down 46% in the last three months, despite being a key player in AI infrastructure. This decline is attributed to slowing growth, margin pressure, and a recent downgrade by Goldman Sachs. While the company projects reaccelerated revenue growth in Q2 fiscal 2026 due to strong AI demand, near-term margin compression from strategic investments and competition presents a key risk, making it a "Hold" for conservative investors.

title: Google stock (GOOG) slips in early trade as Apple Gemini deal meets fresh legal heat
summary: Alphabet's non-voting class C shares (GOOG) fell by about 1.1% despite a recent surge in its stock, as its deal with Apple to integrate Gemini models faces legal scrutiny and market adjustments. The dip comes amid concerns over AI-related legal risks and the broader market's reaction to big bank results. Investors are now looking to Alphabet's upcoming Q4 earnings call on February 4th for updates on ad trends, Google Cloud growth, and Gemini's monetization.

title: HP Inc. call volume above normal and directionally bullish

title: The Zacks Analyst Blog Highlights NVIDIA, Alphabet, Amazon.com and CBL & Associates Properties

title: Moderna says its expects $1.9 billion in 2025 sales amid better-than-expected vaccination rate
summary: Moderna projects $1.9 billion in revenue for 2025, exceeding previous guidance, primarily due to higher-than-anticipated COVID-19 vaccination rates despite political challenges. This financial update was shared at the JPMorgan Healthcare Conference.

title: Wing and Walmart Expand Drone Delivery to 150 New Stores

The initiative highlights the rapid move of drone delivery from an experimental phase to mainstream utility, with Wing also partnering with DoorDash for restaurant deliveries.

Additionally, Kroger will use Customer Experience Agent Studio to enhance customer service by analyzing call interactions and improving associate productivity.

title: Kroger scales generative AI strategy alongside Google Cloud

title: Buy Struggling Netflix Stock, Says Analyst. Why Warner Takeover Fears Are Overblown.

title: Soon you can buy from Google AI results without opening a new site

This initiative aims to streamline the shopping experience from discovery to purchase, with merchants retaining their status as the merchant of record and full ownership of customer relationships and transaction data. Commerce will leverage its Feedonomics data enrichment layer to optimize product feeds for Google's schema, enhancing product visibility and conversion rates within the AI ecosystem.

title: Walmart to expand drone delivery to hundreds of stores

The service, which currently exists in parts of Texas and Atlanta, will extend to major cities like Los Angeles, St. Louis, Cincinnati, and Miami.

title: Data center investments to hit $3 trillion over next five years, says Moody’s By Investing.com

title: 3 Funds for 2026 and Beyond

title: Why RBC Sees Opportunity in F5 Inc. (FFIV) After the Breach-Driven Pullback

title: Zscaler Threat Report Highlights Android and IoT Security Risks
summary: Zscaler's ThreatLabz 2025 report reveals a significant increase in mobile and IoT malware, with over 40 million downloads of malicious Android apps. The report emphasizes the critical need for Zero Trust approaches and AI-powered threat detection to combat these evolving risks.

title: OneAscent Financial Services LLC Sells 5,579 Shares of Alphabet Inc. $GOOG

title: £2bn UK lawsuit accuses Microsoft of overcharging cloud customers - Business Matters
summary: A £2 billion collective legal action has been launched against Microsoft in the UK, alleging that the tech giant overcharged customers using its Windows Server software on rival cloud platforms like AWS, Google Cloud, and Alibaba Cloud. This lawsuit follows findings by the UK's Competition and Markets Authority (CMA) that Microsoft's licensing practices "adversely impact competition," and a procedural hearing is scheduled for December 2025 to determine if the case will proceed to a full trial.

summary: Meta Platforms is nearing new highs as reports surface about its potential acquisition of PlayAI, an AI startup specializing in voice imitation. title: Investing in the ASX's VanEck Wide Moat ETF (MOAT)? Here's what you're buying

This tool, developed using Google Cloud's Vertex AI and Gemini 2.0 Pro, aims to improve viewer search experiences, user retention, and time spent on platforms by offering personalized and superior content recommendations. CineSearch for Business is now available for licensing to OEMs and streaming platforms, addressing industry challenges such as poor discovery leading to subscriber cancellations and long search times.

summary: Evogene announced the completion of its first-in-class generative AI foundation model for small molecule design, developed in collaboration with Google Cloud. This new model, integrated with Evogene's ChemPass AI, addresses the challenge of identifying novel small molecules that meet multiple complex product criteria for pharmaceutical and agriculture applications. The company reports approximately 90% precision in novel molecule designs and plans for version 2.0 with enhanced multi-parameter optimization.

This decision, approved by stockholders, aims to consolidate shares without altering par value or percentage ownership, except for fractional share rounding. The company also recently completed a warrant inducement agreement, raising approximately $2.316 million for working capital.

summary: Plus, an AI-based virtual driver software company for autonomous trucks, announced its plan to go public via a merger with Churchill Capital Corp IX. This strategic move aims to address the $2 trillion trucking freight market by leveraging Physical AI and OEM partnerships with companies like TRATON GROUP, Hyundai, and IVECO.

title: Google cuts trust in Chunghwa Telecom's certificates: What's at stake for internet security chain?
summary: Google has decided to remove default trust for digital certificates issued by Chunghwa Telecom starting July 31, 2025, due to "longstanding patterns of compliance failures." This move, following Mozilla Firefox's earlier consideration of delisting, has significant implications for Chunghwa Telecom, which dominates Taiwan's market, and highlights broader issues in internet security and certificate authority governance. The article explores the function of digital certificates, why browsers can unilaterally delist CAs, and the potential fallout for businesses and users.

Investors are advised to be cautious, overweight value and small-cap stocks, and prepare for potential market downturns despite the current calm. Several sectors and specific stocks are highlighted for their current valuations and performance.

title: As Duolingo Turns to AI, Some Users Say Language App Has Joined ‘The Dark Side’

While the company's CEO, Luis von Ahn, asserts that AI accelerates content creation and allows for wider access, critics argue that AI lacks the nuance of human teachers and could diminish the social and emotional aspects of language learning. Despite user dissatisfaction and threats of boycotts, Duolingo leadership sees AI as crucial for scaling educational content and improving feedback for learners.

Goldman revised its compound annual growth rate forecast, highlighting that while growth may slow, new monetization strategies, particularly in superfan-targeted products and concert ticketing, will be key. Spotify, which holds a significant market share, is expected to benefit from these trends, along with strategic price hikes and product innovation.

title: Google Chrome to distrust Chunghwa Telecom, Netlock certificates in August
summary: Google Chrome will distrust root CA certificates from Chunghwa Telecom and Netlock starting August 1, 2025, due to persistent compliance failures. This change will cause "Your connection is not private" warnings for websites using their certificates, prompting web administrators to switch to trusted Certificate Authorities. This action follows Google's increased scrutiny of CAs and similar decisions against other providers.

title: Chrome to Distrust Chunghwa Telecom and Netlock Certificates
summary: Google announced that its Chrome Root Store will no longer trust digital certificates issued by Chunghwa Telecom and Netlock due to "patterns of concerning behavior observed over the past year." This change will take effect in Chrome 139 for certificates issued after July 31, 2025, and website operators are advised to replace affected certificates to avoid security warnings for users. Google emphasizes that this decision is to preserve the integrity of the Chrome Root Store and ensure user safety.

Elastic's fiscal year 2026 full-year revenue outlook of $1.655 billion to $1.67 billion missed the expected $1.69 billion.

PG&E is actively working on numerous data center projects, particularly in Silicon Valley and the Bay Area, and is conducting further studies across California to accommodate future growth and integrate these large loads efficiently.

The merger is expected to finalize by the end of the current quarter and complete in the third quarter, pending regulatory approvals.

authors: Tim Bohen, Ben Sturgill, Ellis Hobbs

title: Mattel Collaborates with Google Cloud to Enhance Consumer Insights, Fan Engagement, and Product Innovation
summary: Mattel, Inc. has partnered with Google Cloud to leverage its data analytics capabilities, enhancing consumer insights, fan engagement, and product innovation. This collaboration has allowed Mattel to analyze millions of customer touchpoints in real-time, drastically reducing analysis time and enabling hyper-personalized engagement and faster product improvements for brands like Barbie DreamHouse and Fisher-Price Glow and Grow Kick & Play Piano Gym. The partnership highlights a 100x increase in data processing capacity and near-instant decision-making, demonstrating Google Cloud's impact on Mattel's approach to customer feedback and product development.

title: Ambarella, Inc. (AMBA) Ships 30M Edge AI Chips and Pushes Forward in Generative AI Processing
summary: Ambarella, Inc. (AMBA) has shipped 30 million edge AI chips and is making significant advancements in generative AI processing. The company's focus on edge generative AI technology and its third-generation CVflow AI accelerator highlights its leading position as a supplier of edge AI systems-on-chip, supporting GenAI models from 0.5 to 34 billion parameters. This news comes amidst China's efforts to foster open-source AI models, challenging US dominance in AI innovation and expanding access to AI in developing markets.

title: Alphabet: Broad-Based Selling Pushes Stock Into 5-Star Territory
summary: Despite recent stock weakness, Morningstar maintains its $237 fair value estimate for Alphabet, classifying it as materially undervalued with a 5-star rating. The company's high-return-on-ad-spending search business is expected to show resilience during economic uncertainty, and its cloud business is projected to accelerate sales in 2025 as capacity constraints ease. The firm also anticipates monetization of developer interest in its leading-edge LLM, Gemini 2.5, through cloud sales.

title: Alphabet CEO Sundar Pichai sells $5.15 million in company stock
summary: Alphabet CEO Sundar Pichai recently sold approximately $5.15 million in company stock through a pre-established trading plan. The sales occurred while Alphabet's stock traded near its 52-week low, though Wall Street maintains a bullish outlook. Pichai's remaining direct holdings in Alphabet amount to over 2.7 million shares.

title: Rob Arnott on Deep Value and ‘Running Towards Lions’
summary: Rob Arnott, founder of Research Affiliates, discusses his deep-value NIXT ETF which invests in underperforming, deleted stocks, aiming to capitalize on their greater upside potential compared to frothy, expensive additions to indexes. He emphasizes the importance of diversification into cheap alternatives, even if uncomfortable, and views the financial advisor's role as guiding clients away from "stupid mistakes" like performance chasing.

title: JFrog report finds AI growth driving new software supply chain threats
summary: A new report from JFrog Ltd. reveals that the expansion of AI technology is significantly increasing security threats across the software supply chain, coinciding with a rise in malicious AI models and vulnerabilities. The report identifies a "quad-fecta" of security issues, including CVEs, malicious packages, exposed secrets, and misconfigurations, while also highlighting inadequate binary scanning and ongoing issues with open-source security practices. Additionally, the proliferation of security tools is contributing to complexity, suggesting a need for more streamlined approaches to protection.

title: Why AI in Healthcare Hinges On A Solid Data Strategy
summary: This article emphasizes that the effectiveness of AI in healthcare is entirely dependent on a solid data strategy, specifically utilizing FAIR (Findable, Accessible, Interoperable, Reusable) data principles. Experts Aashima Gupta and Ted Slater highlight that without a robust data foundation, AI approaches like Gen AI and Agentic AI will not deliver their full potential, urging healthcare organizations to prioritize data strategy to overcome inefficiencies and inaccuracies.

title: Equities in 2025: Embracing a Broader Landscape
summary: Goldman Sachs Asset Management foresees a broadening landscape of equity market opportunities for active investors in 2025, moving beyond the dominance of US mega-cap tech. The report highlights potential in small-cap companies, developed markets like Japan and Europe, and emerging markets such as India and specific sectors in China. Investors are encouraged to pursue diversified, active strategies and explore long-term themes like reshoring and increased energy demand.
authors: Steve Barry, Alexis Deladerriere, Başak Yavuz

title: Human Augmentation Market to Grow USD 985.13 Billion by 2032, Driven by Advancements in AI, Wearable Technology and Biotechnology | SNS Insider
summary: The Human Augmentation Market is projected to reach USD 985.13 Billion by 2032, growing at a CAGR of 18.02% from 2024, driven by advancements in AI, wearable technology, and biotechnology. This growth is fueled by applications in healthcare, defense, and workplace productivity, with North America currently leading and Asia Pacific expected to be the fastest-growing region. Key players like Samsung Electronics, Google LLC, and Ekso Bionics are prominent in this evolving market, which includes products such as wearable devices, AR/VR technologies, and exoskeletons.

title: NVIDIA Announces Isaac GR00T N1 — the World’s First Open Humanoid Robot Foundation Model — and Simulation Frameworks to Speed Robot Development
summary: NVIDIA announced Isaac GR00T N1, the world’s first open and customizable foundation model for humanoid robots, along with new simulation frameworks like the Isaac GR00T Blueprint and the Newton physics engine. These technologies are designed to accelerate humanoid robot development, making them more adaptable and capable of complex tasks. NVIDIA is collaborating with Google DeepMind and Disney Research on the Newton engine, and the GR00T N1 model is already being adopted by leading humanoid developers.

title: OSRH Stock Plummets to 52-Week Low at $1.31 Amid Market Challenges
summary: Bellevue Life Sciences Acquisition Corp. (OSRH) stock has fallen to a new 52-week low of $1.31, reflecting tumultuous market conditions and an oversold RSI. The company’s market capitalization is now $25.6 million, with a one-year return of -86.51% and a YTD return of -87.55%. In other news, OSR Holdings secured an equity financing agreement with White Lion GBM Innovation Fund, allowing it to sell up to $80 million in common stock to White Lion to enhance its financial flexibility in the medical device industry.

title: Five Investment Themes to Watch in Equity and Alternative for 2025
summary: In 2025, investors are focusing on diversification and risk management due to shifting macroeconomic conditions, a new U.S. administration, and evolving trade policies. Key investment themes include diversifying within U.S. equities, increasing exposure to international equities, particularly in Japan, and utilizing commodities and cryptocurrencies for portfolio diversification and inflation hedging. The article highlights the role of CME Group's various futures and options contracts in managing these investment strategies.

title: Live Nation Loses Bid to Narrow DOJ Ticketmaster Case
summary: A federal judge in New York denied Live Nation Entertainment Inc.'s attempt to narrow the Justice Department’s antitrust case against it, which seeks to break off Ticketmaster. The DOJ and some 30 states allege Live Nation has illegally monopolized the live events industry, controlling a significant portion of concert venues and ticketing. A trial is scheduled for March 2026.
authors: Josh Sisco, Leah Nylen, Chris Dolmetsch

title: Stock Market Today: Dow Sinks 537 Points On Tariff Threats As S&P 500 Corrects; Gold Miners Jump, Meta Triggers Sell Rule (Live Coverage)
summary: The Dow Jones Industrial Average fell 537 points, and the S&P 500 corrected amid new tariff threats from the Trump administration. Gold miners rallied while Home Depot and Meta Platforms experienced sell-offs, with Meta triggering a sell rule. Despite a late attempt by traders to cover short positions, major indexes ended the trading day lower.

title: Alphabet’s John Hennessy sells shares worth over $33,000
summary: John L. Hennessy, a director at Alphabet Inc., recently sold 200 shares of the company's Class C Capital Stock for approximately $33,106. The transaction was conducted under a pre-arranged 10b5-1 trading plan. Despite the sale, InvestingPro analysis suggests Alphabet is currently undervalued, with strong financial health indicators.

title: NextEra mulls doubling $20 billion investment in Texas in next few years
summary: NextEra Energy is considering doubling its $20 billion investment in Texas in the coming years due to a surge in U.S. power demand, particularly from Big Tech's data centers and industrial electrification. The state, already a major power producer, could see electricity demand double by 2030, and NextEra is exploring land in the Permian Basin for new developments.

title: Is it time to buy the Magnificent Seven?
summary: The "Magnificent Seven" tech stocks have experienced a significant selloff, making some of them appear undervalued according to Morningstar's fair value metrics. While Meta, Amazon, Microsoft, and Alphabet are now rated as buys, Nvidia and Tesla are fairly valued, and Apple remains overvalued. Morningstar strategists still recommend underweighting growth stocks overall, favoring value stocks due to market volatility and slowing economic growth.

title: Tech Moves: Longtime Google leader Umesh Shankar joins Microsoft as new corporate VP
summary: Umesh Shankar, a veteran leader from Google, has joined Microsoft AI as a corporate vice president of engineering, focusing on privacy and security for the Copilot AI assistant. This move is part of a trend of Google executives moving to Microsoft AI. The article also details other significant personnel changes at Remitly, Crelate, Bloomberg, Pioneer Square Labs, Seattle Aquarium, Built Oregon, Fred Hutch Cancer Center, and Trove.

title: US OPEN: Selloff on Monday as Uncertainty Continues
summary: US markets experienced a selloff on Monday, with major indices showing negative performance and the VIX fear gauge climbing, indicating rising market anxiety. European markets also saw significant declines, while specific company news included Google Chrome divestiture pressures, plummeting Tesla China sales, Rocket Companies acquiring Redfin, and Robinhood settling with FINRA for $30 million.

title: Anthropic Stake for the Masses Is Latest ETF Industry Gambit
summary: KraneShares has acquired a direct stake in Anthropic, a privately held AI company and competitor to OpenAI, through one of its exchange-traded funds. This move combines the surging interest in artificial intelligence with the growing trend of offering private assets to a broader investment audience. Anthropic recently secured funding at a valuation exceeding $60 billion.

title: China bans imports of Illumina's gene sequencers right after Trump tariff action
summary: China announced a ban on imports of genetic sequencers from U.S. medical equipment maker Illumina, effective immediately after the U.S. imposed additional tariffs on Chinese goods. This ban is part of China's retaliatory measures and follows Illumina's placement on Beijing's "unreliable entity" list. The move has led to a significant jump in shares for Illumina's Chinese rivals, MGI and BGI.

title: Alphabet director Frances Arnold sells shares worth $20,606
summary: Alphabet Inc. director Frances Arnold sold 121 shares of the company's Class C Capital Stock for a total of $20,606 on February 28, 2025, as part of a pre-arranged trading plan. Following the sale, Arnold still holds 16,938 shares of Class C stock and various Class C Google Stock Units. The transaction occurred while Alphabet's stock declined 11% year-to-date, though InvestingPro analysis suggests it may be slightly undervalued.

title: Earnings call transcript: Eventbrite Q4 2024 misses EPS forecast, stock drops
summary: Eventbrite Inc. (NYSE: EB) reported a wider-than-expected loss in Q4 2024 with an EPS of -$0.09, missing the -$0.05 forecast, despite revenue slightly surpassing expectations at $76.5 million. The stock subsequently dropped nearly 12% in after-hours trading. The company outlined 2025 as a "year of transition," focusing on expanding product offerings and market presence, including reintroducing free ticket listings and investing in Eventbrite Ads, while anticipating a revenue range of $295 million to $310 million for the full year.

title: SpaceX launches Intuitive Machines’ 2nd Moon lander, 3 rideshare spacecraft
summary: SpaceX successfully launched Intuitive Machines' second Nova-C lunar lander, Athena, along with three rideshare spacecraft, marking a return to the Moon for the Houston-based company. The mission, part of NASA's CLPS Program, aims for a lunar landing on March 6 at Mons Mouton near the Moon's South Pole, carrying several scientific and commercial payloads, including the Micro Nova Hopper named Grace. This flight builds on lessons learned from its predecessor, Odysseus, focusing on improved operational readiness and a robust global communications network.

title: VIG, VOX: 2 Funds to Consider as Vanguard Becomes the King of ETFs
summary: Vanguard’s VOO ETF has surpassed State Street’s SPY ETF to become the world’s largest ETF, driven by its lower expense ratio. This shift highlights Vanguard's growing dominance in the ETF market. Investors are advised to consider two Vanguard ETFs, VIG and VOX, both offering over 10% upside potential in the next year, with VIG focused on dividend appreciation and VOX on communication services.

title: Mark Zuckerberg Offloads Meta Shares Worth $14.4 Million In February
summary: Mark Zuckerberg sold 17,855 shares of Meta Platforms Inc. Class A common stock worth approximately $14.4 million on February 14, at prices between $726.68 and $740.71. These transactions were executed under a pre-established trading plan and follow previous sales in late December 2024. Despite these sales, Meta demonstrates strong financial health with a high gross profit margin and increased quarterly dividends.

title: Arista Networks’ growth accelerates, driven by big AI investments
summary: Arista Networks Inc. reported a significant increase in profit and revenue for its fourth quarter, driven by strong demand for advanced networking infrastructure supporting AI workloads. The company beat Wall Street estimates for both profit and revenue, with CEO Jayshree Ullal highlighting fiscal 2024 as a "remarkable year." Despite a conservative forecast for the current quarter which caused a temporary stock dip, analysts remain optimistic about Arista's long-term prospects due to continued AI investments from major hyperscale customers and effective cost management.
